==English==
===Intransitive verb phrase===
'''to come out of the closet'''

#To tell others about one's [[homosexuality]] or [[bisexuality]], in instances where such a [[sexual orientation]] had been a guarded secret kept from all or most others, or from [[significant other]]s.
#To tell others about a minority or disapproved-of belief, preference, etc., in instances where such a belief, preference, etc. had been a guarded secret kept from all or most others, or from significant others:  ''She finally came out of the closet to her religious family regarding her atheism.''

